{
  "stem": "22869.6",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I mean, it wasn't cooked, but with some dried onions and some meat, we had a few days-- we had food as we were going on this plane-- this train, rather.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "I don't know why I'm always mixing up 'plane' with 'train.'",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And we kept on being on this train day in, day out again, moving in, until we wandered into-- now I'm talking about we are already in the end of, the midst of April 1945.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And they-- they brought us into Austria.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And one day, probably they had no more way-- places where to go-- they caught up because we were not too far away where the American lines were fighting already.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So they put-- took the whole train one day, and they put us with the SS that were guarding us on a [SPEAKING GERMAN], which is a German word for a dead-end track.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It's a track where it's-- it does not interfere with the traffic of-- of-- all the other trains.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And if you want to put away for repairs a few of this details there from the train, you put them in a place like this, and it's not being bothered-- it doesn't bother anybody.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And that's the way we were sitting day in and day out.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The only food that we had is, like I said, the leftovers from this.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "No water, nothing.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And every day, of course, we hear-- we hear the-- the-- the shooting, right and left.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We were--we knew we are in the-- in the front lines.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "We didn't know exactly where we were.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And the SS men come out from the trains every day to taunt us a little bit, to heckle us, you know, to heckle us and to make some remarks and something like this.",
      "word_count": 34
    }
  ],
